      "content": "Absolute Eosinophil Count\nTest\nAbsolute eosinophil count is a blood test that measures the number of eosinophils (white blood cells).\nThis test is performed to detect certain allergies, infections, and other diseases as eosinophils in our blood become active in such medical conditions.\nEnquire Now\nAbsolute Eosinophil Count Tests\nAbsolute Lymphocyte Count\nThe Absolute Lymphocyte Count test is a blood test that calculates the level of Absolute Lymphocyte Count of the blood. This test detects Infectious Mononucleosis, Leukemia, Lymphoma, and Tuberculosis.\nAbsolute Neutrophil Count\nAbsolute Neutrophil Count or ANC is a blood test that measures the total neutrophil count to see if it's\nabove or below the normal count. This test can be performed to detect the different organisms present in blood and determine whether the body's immune system is working efficiently.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nWB-EDTA (3 ml)\nCell counter/microscopy\nA\nDaily\n4 Hours\n100\nImmune system changes\nCell Impedence\n150\nIn evaluating Allergic\nreactions.",
