      "content": "Reticulocyte Count\nTest\nA reticulocyte count is a blood test that measures the number of reticulocytes in the blood. Reticulocytes are immature red blood cells ( red blood cells that aren't fully developed yet). This particular blood test can be done to know the following:\n- To determine if someone has a medical condition that causes a low number of red blood cells, such as anemia.\n- To determine if the bone marrow in the body is working well enough to produce new red blood cells.\nIf an individual has had a blood transfusion, the doctor must inform this since it affects the reticulocyte\ntest results.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nWB-EDTA (3 ml)\nNew Methylene Blue Stained\nSmear Microscopic Examination\nA\nDaily\n4 Hours\n180\n-",
