      "excerpt": "Amylase – Serum Test Amylase - Serum A serum amylase test measures the amount of amylase in your blood. Amylase is an enzyme, or special protein, that helps digest food. Most of the amylase is produced in the pancreas and salivary glands. Hence, a small amount...",
      "content": "Amylase – Serum\nTest\nAmylase - Serum\nA serum amylase test measures the amount of amylase in your blood. Amylase is an enzyme, or special protein, that helps digest food. Most of the amylase is produced in the pancreas and salivary glands. Hence, a small amount of amylase in the blood is normal.\nThis test is done to identify abnormal amylase levels in the blood, which indicates a disorder of the pancreas, an infection, alcoholism, or another medical condition.\nEnquire Now\nAmylase - Serum Tests\nAmylase-Body Fluid\nThis amylase test can be performed on the patient's other body fluids such as Pancreatic Cyst Fluid, etc. This test can even be used to detect pancreatic cancer.\nAmylase-Urine-Random\nAn amylase urine test is usually recommended along with or after a serum amylase test. Urine amylase\nresults can help diagnose disorders related to pancreatic and salivary glands.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nSpectrophotometry\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n400\nTo diagnose & monitor\npancreatitis & other\npancreatic diseases\nBody Fluids (1 ml)\nUrine (25ml)\nRandom sample required.\nTo diagnose Pancreatitis &\nintestinal obstruction",
