      "excerpt": "Bilirubin (Total + Direct) Test Bilirubin (Total + Direct) A bilirubin test measures the levels of bilirubin compounds in an individual&'s bloodstream. A blood test can measure two forms of bilirubin: conjugated (direct) and unconjugated (indirect). The major...",
      "content": "Bilirubin (Total + Direct)\nTest\nA bilirubin test measures the levels of bilirubin compounds in an individual&'s bloodstream. A blood test can measure two forms of bilirubin: conjugated (direct) and unconjugated (indirect).\nThe major difference between both of them is that the direct bilirubin is water-soluble, while indirect bilirubin is insoluble in water.\nEnquire Now\nBilirubin (Total + Direct) Tests\nComparing the below three results, the doctor can identify health conditions such as liver damage, liver disease, jaundice (yellowing of the skin/eyes), pancreatic cancer, or gallbladder cancer.\nBilirubin Direct\n\"Direct\" or \"conjugated\" bilirubin indicates that sugar has been attached to it.\nBilirubin Indirect\n\"Indirect\" or \"unconjugated\" bilirubin indicates the absence of sugar.\nBilirubin Total\nAltogether, the total amount of bilirubin in our body is called \"total\" bilirubin.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nSpectrophotometry\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n150\nProtect the collection tube\nfrom direct light. To Monitor\nLiver disorders\n-",
