      "link": "https://mediscanlab.com/anti-mullerian-hormone",
      "excerpt": "Anti – Mullerian Hormone (AMH) Test Anti - Mullerian Hormone (AMH) This test measures the levels of Anti-Müllerian hormone in an individual's bloodstream. Anti-Müllerian hormone (AMH) is a hormone produced by reproductive organs, including the testicles in mal...",
      "content": "Anti – Mullerian Hormone (AMH)\nTest\nAnti - Mullerian Hormone (AMH)\nThis test measures the levels of Anti-Müllerian hormone in an individual's bloodstream. Anti-Müllerian hormone (AMH) is a hormone produced by reproductive organs, including the testicles in males and the ovaries in females. Doctors recommend this test to assess a woman's fertility (ovarian reserve or egg count). This test can also be performed to:\n- Predict the start of menopause\n- Find out the reason for early menopause\n- Help find out the reason for amenorrhea\n- Help diagnose polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)\n- Check infants with genitals that are not clearly identified as male or female\n- Monitor types of ovarian cancer\nEnquire Now\nAnti - Mullerian Hormone (AMH) Tests\nAntiStreptolysin O Titres(ASO)\nThe ASO titer test measures the number of antibodies produced in the body in response to a toxin\nknown as streptolysin O. this test is usually performed to check for a strep infection.\nAnti Thyroglobulin Antibody (ATG)\nThis test is used to measure the levels of thyroglobulin antibodies in your bloodstream. Abnormal levels may indicate an auto-immune disorder.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nElectro Chemiluminescence\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n1900\nInfertility , Age , Relevant\nPCOD. To monitor Systumic\nlupus erythematosus (SLE)\nAnti Streptolysin O Titres(ASO)\nImmunoturbidometry\n300\nTo diagnose Strept\nthroat,Glomerular\nnephritis,rheumatic\nfever,bacterial endocarditis.\n1300\nTo diagnose Grave’s\ndisease,Hashimoto’s\nthyroiditis,Myxedema, thyroid\ncancer.",
