      "excerpt": "Bence Jones Protein (BJ Protein) Test Bence Jones Protein (BJ Protein) This test measures the presence of Bence Jones protein in a person's urine sample. This particular protein is a building block of antibodies produced by cancerous tumors. Therefore, the BJ...",
      "content": "Bence Jones Protein (BJ Protein)\nTest\nThis test measures the presence of Bence Jones protein in a person's urine sample. This particular protein is a building block of antibodies produced by cancerous tumors.\nTherefore, the BJ protein test is one of the several tests used to diagnose a type of blood cancer known as multiple myeloma.\nEnquire Now\nBence Jones Protein Tests\nBeta -HCG-Free - Serum\nThe beta HCG-free test is used to detect the presence of the Human Chorionic Gonadotropin hormone\nin the blood sample of a woman. This hormone is produced by the placenta during pregnancy, thusmaking it a useful pregnancy test. This HCF test forms the basis of the pregnancy testing kits available in pharmacies. Apart from evaluating pregnancy, the beta-hCG test can also be used during evaluations of fertility treatments.\nBeta-Human Chorionic Gonadotropin Hormone\nThe placenta produces this hormone during pregnancy. Since the hormone is released in the\nbloodstream and urine ten days post-conception, an above-normal level can confirm pregnancy.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nUrine Random (20ml)\nHeat Precipitation Test\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n550\nDiagnosis of multiple myeloma\n& other similar diseases\nSerum (1ml)\nChemiluminescence\n1000\nClinical History Required\nBeta- Human Chorionic Gonodotropin\nHormone\nElecroChemiluminescence\n950",
