      "content": "Chloride\nTest\nChloride - Serum\nThe body strives to maintain a balanced acid-base (pH) equilibrium. However, certain circumstances can result in an imbalance.\nEnquire Now\nChloride Tests\nChloride -CSF\nThis test can help see if you have metabolic alkalosis, which can occur if your bodily tissues become overly alkaline.\nChloride-Urine-24 hrs\nIn a 24-hour collection, the usual range is 110 to 250 mEq per day. This range is determined by the amount of salt and liquids consumed.\nChloride-Urine-Random\nThe findings for the test may differ based on your age, gender, health history, the method utilized\nfor the test, and other factors. The normal range for a random urine sample is 20 to 40 mEq/L. A urine sample is needed for these tests. Your healthcare practitioner will instruct you on how to get a sample for this test.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nISE\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n130\nAcid Base balance\nCSF (1ml)\nR/F\n200\nCSF Acid base balance\nUrine (25ml)\n24 Hr Urine Volume Required\nUrine (5 ml)\n-",
