      "content": "Cholesterol\nTest\nThough necessary in smaller amounts, larger quantities of cholesterol may clog the arteries and cause cardiac ailments.\nCholesterol tests are performed to detect heart wellness and problems due to clogged/narrowed arteries due to cholesterol.\nEnquire Now\nCholesterol Tests\nCholesterol - Total\nIt is usually the first prescribed test. It measures all kinds of cholesterols in the body.\nCholesterol - HDL\nIt is as good as high. The High-Density Lipoprotein(HDL), also called the \"good\" cholesterol, lowers\nthe risks of cardiac diseases.\nCholesterol - LDL\nLow-Density Lipoprotein(LDL) is known to clog heart arteries. It should be as low as possible. Otherwise, it can lead to heart disease and stroke.\nCholesterol - VLDL\nVLDL has a maximum amount of triglycerides. It is bad cholesterol as it aids the cholesterol buildup on the artery walls.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nDirect Enzyme Assay\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n250\n12-14 Hrs Fasting Required.\nTo determinerisk of\ndeveloping heart disease\nCalculation\n12-14 Hrs Fasting Required,\nbad cholesterol increased\nlevel causes CAD\nCHOD-PAP\n140\nTo screen for risk of\ndeveloping heart disease.\nCholesterol VLDL\n-",
