      "content": "Complete Blood Count\nTest\nThis most commonly prescribed blood test measures the health of all types of cells in the blood.\nA few drops of blood from a vein are sufficient for the test. This test tells about the WBC count, RBC count, hemoglobin, hematocrit, platelet count, mean platelet volume, etc.\nEnquire Now\nComplete Blood Count Tests\nComplete Blood Test(CBC) with PS\nThe CBC with PS( Peripheral Blood Smear) is a laboratory procedure in which a blood sample is observed under the microscope to check the circulating blood cells(WBC, RBC, etc.) if they do look normal. This test is required to diagnose hematological issues in the patient.\nComplete Urine Examination\nThis series of tests is similar to CBC but done on urine instead of blood. It is used to check diabetes, renal issues, UT infections, etc. A cup of urine or all the urine collected over 12/24 hours may be required for testing.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nComplete Blood Count (CBC)\nWB-EDTA (3 ml)\nElectrical Impedence , Microscopy\nA\nDaily\n4 Hours\n250\nClinical History Mandatory.\nGeneral health status &\nscreen certain disorders like\nanemias\nComplete Blood Count (CBC) with PS\n300\nGeneral health status & screen\ncertain disorders like anemias\nComplete Urine Analysis (CUE)\nUrine (5ml)\nReagent strip reflectance and microscopy\n110\nEvaluating urinary tract\ninfection,diabetes & certain\nkidney disorders..",
