      "excerpt": "Creatinine Test Creatinine A creatinine test is done to analyze the performance of kidneys. Healthy kidneys filter out creatinine from the blood. Creatinine Tests Creatine Kinase MB This test measures the quantity of creatine kinase(CK) in the blood. High leve...",
      "content": "Creatinine\nTest\nA creatinine test is done to analyze the performance of kidneys. Healthy kidneys filter out creatinine from the blood.\nCreatinine Tests\nCreatine Kinase MB\nThis test measures the quantity of creatine kinase(CK) in the blood. High levels of CK indicate heart damage. This test makes the diagnosis of a heart attack.\nCreatinine- (24 Hrs Urine)\nIn this test, urine produced in 24 hrs is used to analyze the kidneys. It is done to get a more accurate value of the creatinine level in the urine.\nCreatinine Clearance\nThis test involves a collection of the urine over 24 hours and drawing out of the blood. It is done to determine the amount of creatinine filtered by the kidneys.\nCreatinine Kinase (CPK)\nThis test is performed to analyze the levels of enzymes in your blood. It is done to diagnose a heart attack or any damage to the heart muscle.\nCreatinine- Spot Urine\nThis test determines the quantity of creatinine in the urine. The waste product of muscle metabolism is creatinine. Your doctor can use the test to see how well your kidneys are working. This is helpful in identifying or ruling out renal disease and other kidney-related illnesses.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nCreatine Kinase MB (CK-MB)\nSerum (1ml)\nImmunoinhibition\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n500\nClinical History Required\nCretinine amido hydrolase\n130\nTo diagnose & monitor renal\nfunction.\nUrine (25ml)\n400\n24 Hr Urine Volume\nCreatinine Clearence Test\nSerum (1ml)/Urine (5 ml)\nSpectrophotometry & Calculation\n550\n24 Hr Urine Volume/To\nevaluate kidney dysfunction.\nUV-Enzymatic\nMyocardial infarction &\nmuscular dystrophy\nCreatinine-Spot Urine\n300\nRandom sample required",
