      "content": "Cytology –Fluids Malignant cell\nTest\nIf the diseases are diagnosed by examining the single-cell or clusters of cells, it is called the cytology test. Generally, this test is performed to diagnose cancerous or precancerous cells.\nIf the cells are found to be abnormal, then it is a sign of cancer. This test is recommended when there is a fluid buildup in the body.\nEnquire Now\nCytology -PAP\nA PAP test is performed to identify precancerous cells in the cervix or colon of the abdomen. Generally, it is performed on women for the diagnosis of Cervical cancer.\nIt can also detect changes in the cervical cells that indicate future cancer.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nAscitic Fluid, Pleural Fluid, Synovial\nFluid, Peritoneal Fluid (1 ml)\nPAP Staining & Microscopy\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n500\n-\nPAP Smear-Fixed\nA",
