      "content": "Dengue\nTest\nDengue - NS1 Antigen, Dengue IgG Antibody, Dengue IgM Antibody\nThe Dengue Antigen NS1, IgG, and IgM tests measure the dengue virus or the antibodies produced to fight the virus. This test is performed if you have a fever after traveling to a tropical or subtropical area where dengue is excessive or has a dengue-endemic.\nFor this test, no prior preparation is required. A sample of your blood is obtained and tested for dengue.\nThe detection of each antibody indicates the following:\n- IgM - Primary Dengue\n- IgG and IgM - Early Secondary Dengue or Late Primary\n- IgG - Past Dengue of Secondary Dengue\nIn the first 5-days of fever, getting an NS1 Antigen test is advisable. If the fever prolongs to 7-10 days, the Dengue Antibody tests should be done.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nDengue - NS1 Antigen\nSerum (1 ml)\nImmunoChromatography\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n500\nTo dianose Dengue fever\nDengue IgG Antibody\nDengue IgM Antibody",
