      "content": "Differential Leukocyte Count\nTest\nA Differential Leukocyte Count (DLC) is a blood test measuring the percentage of types of White Blood Cells (WBC) present in your blood. White Blood Cells are significant for a strong immune system. This test not only measures the WBCs but detects irregularity and immaturity in WBC count, indicating diseases like anemia, leukemia, and related infections.\nThe types of WBC measured under this test are:\n- Neutrophils\n- Eosinophils\n- Basophils\n- Lymphocytes\n- Monocytes\n- A complete blood count test for health check-ups is conducted\n- Diagnosing diseases that reduce WBC count\n- Diagnosing infections and inflammations due to WBCMonitoring functioning of the bone marrow\n- Monitoring ongoing chemotherapy treatment\nNo prior preparation is required on your part. A sample of your blood will be drawn and tested.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nDifferantial Leukocyte Count (DLC)\nWB-EDTA (3 ml)\nCell counter/microscopy\nA\nDaily\n4 Hours\n130\n-",
