      "content": "Globulin\nTest\nThe immune system produces proteins in the blood, known as Globulin. Globulin is responsible for fighting diseases, clotting blood, and liver functioning. Globulin tests are used to diagnose the following:\n- Kidney Disease\n- Liver Diseases\n- Autoimmune Disorders\n- Problems in nutrition\n- Diagnose a few types of cancer\nGlobulin tests are advised either as regular check-up tests or to inspect symptoms like jaundice, nausea, itching, loss of appetite, fluid build-up, and frequent fatigue. Blood is drawn from your veins for this test.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1 ml)\nSpectrophotometry\nA/R\n-\n4 Hours\n250\nScreening for\nHypergammaglobulinemia",
