      "excerpt": "Gamma Glutamyl Transferase Test Gamma Glutamyl Transferase A Gamma Glutamyl Transferase (GGT) measures the level of GGT in the blood. GGT is an enzyme that is found in the liver. It leaks into the bloodstream if there are damages to the liver. The presence of...",
      "content": "Gamma Glutamyl Transferase\nTest\nA Gamma Glutamyl Transferase (GGT) measures the level of GGT in the blood. GGT is an enzyme that is found in the liver. It leaks into the bloodstream if there are damages to the liver. The presence of high levels of GGT indicates liver diseases.\nThe test is required to:\n- Diagnose liver diseases\n- Identify Bile Duct Blockages\n- Determine whether a bone disorder is a cause for the damage\n- Monitor alcohol abuse\nIf you have symptoms like fatigue, nausea, weakness, jaundice, or loss of appetite, this test isrecommended. No prior preparations are required. A blood sample is taken for the test.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nGamma Glutamyl Transferase (GGT)\nSerum (1 ml)\nIFCC\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n250\nTo detemine liver function &\nbiliary obstruction.",
