      "content": "HCV (Rapid)\nTest\nHCV Rapid tests are performed on an individual to detect the presence of hepatitis C antibodies (anti-HCV) in human serum. As the name implies, the test is used as a vital diagnostic test when a hepatitis C\ninfection is suspected. Hepatitis C is a contagious liver infection caused by the hepatitis C virus (HCV) and can be transmitted through contaminated blood.\nHCV Rapid Tests are safe, quick, very sensitive, thus giving out results in less than 20 minutes. The anti- HCV Rapid Test is for in-vitro diagnostic use only and is based on the principle of an inter-second antibody enzyme immunoassay for detecting anti-HCV in blood serum or plasma.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1 ml)\nImmunochromatography\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n400\nDetection of HCV Antibodies",
