      "content": "Helicobacter Pylori IgG\nTest\nA Helicobacter Pylori IgG test is performed to detect the presence of H Pylori Antibody IgG. Doctors usually recommend this test to diagnose the cause of peptic ulcers in the duodenum or stomach of an individual. The Helicobacter Pylori IgG can also be used to diagnose the causes of chronic gastritis symptoms, gastrointestinal pain, and discomfort.\nH Pylori antibody confirms the presence of Helicobacter Pylori infection in a person’s stomach. It weakens the stomach’s natural protective lining, and the gastric acids damage the healthy stomach, forming ulcers. This might also lead to stomach cancer. The Helicobacter Pylori IgG test can also be used to evaluate the effectiveness of the treatment.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nHelicobacter Pylorii IgM\nSerum (1 ml)\nImmunochromatography\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n750\nGastritis & duodenal ulcers",
