      "content": "Hepatitis A virus IgM\nTest\nHepatitis A virus IgM (HAV- IgM)\nHepatitis A virus IgM (HAV) test is performed to detect the presence of Hepatitis A virus in the bloodstream.\nIgM antibodies are produced against the virus within weeks of infection, and hence this test determines whether a person is infected with the Hepatitis A virus (HAV).\nEnquire Now\nHepatitis A virus IgM (HAV- IgM) Tests\nHepatitis A virus-IgG (HAV IgG)\nThis test is performed to detect IgG antibodies in the blood produced due to Hepatitis A infection.\nHepatitis B Envelope Antigen (HBeAg)\nThis is a blood test conducted to detect the presence of Hepatitis B e-antigen (HBeAg). This test is\nconducted to diagnose Hepatitis B infection in the initial stages of infection in a patient.\nHepatitis B surface Antibody Total (Anti HBs)\nThis test is conducted to detect total surface antibodies of Hepatitis B virus infection.\nHepatitis B Surface antigen (HBsAg)\nThis is a rapid test for detecting hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) in blood serum, plasma, or whole\nblood.\nThis test detects the HBsAg in an individual’s bloodstream to confirm Hepatitis B virus infection.\nHepatitis E virus - IgM (HEV IgM)\nThis ELISA test is performed on a Blood sample to detect the Hepatitis E IgM antibody (HEV IgM). This\ntest is used to diagnose Hepatitis E virus infection.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1 ml)\nImmunochromatography\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n950\nTo diagnose chronic liver\ndisease\nELFA\n1000\nTo diagnose Hepatitis\nHepatitis B surface Antibody Total\n(Anti HBs)\n1350\nHepatitis B Surface Antigen(Rapid)\n150\nCLIA\n300\n1250",
