      "content": "Iron\nTest\nIron tests are not individual tests but a group of clinical chemistry laboratory tests used to analyze body iron stores or the iron level in blood serum. Iron tests are also commonly known as the iron panel, iron profile, iron indices, iron status, or iron studies.\nIron is an essential mineral for the human body as it's used for the production of red blood cells. Doctors prescribe having an iron test to check whether a person has abnormal iron levels in their bloodstream.\nWhen detected, both high and low iron levels than normal can indicate serious health complications such as hemochromatosis.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nPyridyl Azo dye\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n500\nEvaluating Microcytic\nanemia",
