      "content": "KOH Preparation for Fungal Elements\nTest\nKOH Preparation for Fungal Elements (Wet Mount)\nThe KOH Wet Mount is a medical chemistry test that detects fungal elements in a given sample. The samples can be skin, nails, hair, ear discharge, sputum, etc. This is a presumptive diagnosis of fungal diseases like ringworm, aspergillosis, dermatomycosis, mucormycosis, otomycosis, and so on.\nKOH preparation:\n- The specimen is emulsified in a drop of 20% KOH on a glass slide. The sample should not be\nbigger than 5 mm long and 2 mm wide.\n- The slide is then heat-sealed over a bunsen burner.\n- The smear is covered with a coverslip and left for 5-10 minutes.\n- As soon as the specimen has cleared, it is examined under a clinical microscope. The fungal\nelements are demonstrated as shining elements in the smear.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\n(Wet Mount)\nUrine (5-10 ml) in sterile\nscrew capped container\nMicroscopy\nR(48hrs)\nDaily\nNext Day (11:00)\n200\n-\nSwabs (1-2 Nos.) in Sterile\nPUS (1-3 ml) in sterile\nSputum (3-5 ml) in sterile\nBody Fluids (1-2 ml) in\nsterile screw capped container\nCSF (1-2 ml) in sterile\nSkin Scrappings (1 g, min) in\nNails (1 g, min) in sterile\nHair (10 Strands) in sterile",
