      "content": "Lactate Dehydrogenase (LDH)\nTest\nLactate Dehydrogenase (LDH)- Ascitic Fluid\nThis test is used to measure the enzyme lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) levels in the ascitic fluid. The LDH enzyme is used to convert sugar into energy within the cells.\nThus, abnormal levels of LDH indicated possible trauma to the abdomen, malignancies, pancreatic, liver, or kidney diseases, etc.\nEnquire Now\nLactate Dehydrogenase (LDH) Tests\nLactate Dehydrogenase (LDH)-CSF\nIt measures LDH enzyme levels in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). This test is used to diagnose several\nneurological disorders.\nLactate Dehydrogenase (LDH)- Pleural Fluid\nThis test measures LDH levels in the pleural fluid to diagnose cellular inflammation or cellular injury.\nLactate Dehydrogenase (LDH)-Serum\nThis test measures LDH levels in the blood serum to diagnose any cellular damage.\nLactate-CSF\nThis test measures lactate levels in the CSF fluid. Elevated levels of lactate in CSF might indicate medical\nconditions like cerebral glycolysis or hypoxia associated with bacterial meningitis, cerebral infection, etc.\nLactate-Plasma\nThis test measures lactate levels in blood serum to diagnose medical conditions like tissue\nhypoperfusion and hypoxia.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nLactate Dehyderogenase (LDH)-\nAscitic Fluid\nAscitic Fluid (1ml)\nUV-Enzymatic\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n400\nSend Serum Samples Also/\nTuberculosis pertonitis\nLactate Dehyderogenase (LDH)-CSF\nCSF (1ml)\nMeningitis & Encephalitis\nPleural Fluid\nPleural Fluid (1ml)\nTissue damage in lungs\nCerebrospinal vascular\naccident,stroke,heart\nattack.hemolytic anemia\nSerum (1ml)\nLactate Oxidase-Peroxidase\n550\nTo diagnose Bacterial\nmeningitis\nNa Heparin Plasma (1ml)\nSeparate Plasma\nImmediately/ Hypoxia,\nCongestive heart failure,\nhepatic problems, Ischemia,\nLung diseases.",
