      "content": "Leptospira Antibody\nTest\nLeptospira IgG Antibody\nA Leptospira-IgG test is a blood test that is performed to detect the anti-Leptospira IgG antibody. It is an ELISA test with high sensitivity (>99%); and specificity (>96%). This test is performed to confirm Leptospirosis in humans.\nLeptospirosis is the most common zoonotic disease (transferred from animals to humans). The causative agents of this disease are the bacteria Leptospirainterrogans or leptospiraborgpetersenii.\nLeptospira IgM Antibody\nSimilar to the Leptospira-IgM test, this test is an ELISA test to detect the presence of Leptospira IgM antibodies in a person’s blood.\nBoth Leptospira IgG and IgM tests are primary tests recommended by doctors to confirm Leptospirosis.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1 ml)\nImmunochromatography\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n650\nTo diagnose Acute\nleptospirosis",
