      "content": "Urea\nTest\nUrea and creatinine levels are used to assess how the kidneys’ operation in the body and to keep track of individuals who have damaged kidneys or are on dialysis. When someone has a non-specific sickness, urea may be utilised in a panel of tests as part of a routine group of testing.\nUrea-Urine-24 hrs:\nThe identification of renal problems is aided by a 24-hour urine collection. It's commonly used to determine how much creatinine passes through the kidneys. This method is used to quantify protein, hormones, minerals, and other chemical components.\nUrine collection for 24 hours can be done as an outpatient procedure. This means you'll be returning home the same day; however this collection could also be done while you're in the hospital.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nUrease UV\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n100\nRenal function\nUrea-Urine-24 hrs\nUrine (25ml)\n200\nTo diagnose Renal\ndisorders",
