      "content": "Uric Acid\nTest\nUric Acid The amount of uric acid in your blood is determined by a uric acid blood test, often known as a serum uric acid measurement. The test can reveal how well your body creates and eliminates uric acid. Uric acid is a chemical that is formed when your body breaks down foods that contain purines, which are organic substances.\nA majority of uric acid is dissolved in the blood, filtered by the kidneys, and then excreted through the urine. The body can manufacture too much uric acid or not filter it out enough at times. Hyperuricemia is the term for a condition in which your body produces too much uric acid.\nUric acid - Urine-24 hrs:\nThe test can reveal how well your body creates and eliminates uric acid. To test your urine over a period of 24 hours, your doctor may advise you to perform both to confirm a diagnosis.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nUricase\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n350\nTo diagnose Gout disaese\nUric acid - Urine-24 hrs\nUrine (25ml)",
