      "excerpt": "Vitamin – B12 Test Vitamin - B12 Vitamin B-12 is essential for a number of bodily functions, including neuron function, DNA synthesis, and the creation of red blood cells. If a person's vitamin B-12 levels fall outside of the usual range, they should seek trea...",
      "content": "Vitamin – B12\nTest\nVitamin - B12\nVitamin B-12 is essential for a number of bodily functions, including neuron function, DNA synthesis, and the creation of red blood cells. If a person's vitamin B-12 levels fall outside of the usual range, they should seek treatment.\nThe deficiency of Vitamin B12 can result in neurological symptoms, as well as fatigue, constipation, and weight loss. B-12 levels that are too high could indicate liver illness, diabetes, or other ailments.\nUnusually high vitamin B-12 levels can be a sign of liver illness, diabetes, or some kinds of leukaemia. A doctor may utilise the results of a vitamin B-12 test to assist them establish a diagnosis.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nElectro Chemiluminescence\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n1100\nProtect serum from light\nduring collection, storage,\nand shipment",
