      "content": "Electrolyte Profile\nTest\nElectrolyte Profile - Serum Chloride, Potassium, Sodium\nA chloride and other electrolytes, such as potassium, sodium, and bicarbonate, are measured in an electrolyte panel.\nIf you have signs of acid or fluid imbalance, such as vomiting over an extended length of time, you may need a chloride blood test.\nEnquire Now\nElectrolyte Profile - Urine Chloride, Potassium, Sodium\nA urine sodium test determines whether the amount of sodium in a sample of your urine is within normal limits.\nToo much or too little salt can indicate a problem with your kidneys or another health concern. They may ask you to perform a sodium urine test after you've already taken a sodium blood test and received abnormal findings.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nElectrolyte Profile - Serum Chloride,\nPotassium, Sodium\nSerum (1ml)\nIon Selective Electrode\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n600\nElectrolyte balance,Hypo &\nhyper natremia\nUrine (5ml)\nDehydration/Electrolyte\nbalance",
