      "content": "Fertility Profile – I\nTest\nFertility Profile - I\nBlood samples can be analysed for a hormone called progesterone to see if you're ovulating. The test's timing is determined by how regular your period is.\nEnquire Now\nFertility Profile - I Tests\nFollicle Stimulating Hormone (FSH)\nThis test determines how much follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) is present in your blood. FSH assists in the management of a woman's menstrual cycle and stimulates egg production in the\novaries.\nLuteinising Hormone (LH)\nA luteinizing hormone test may be ordered for a variety of reasons. An LH test is a part of an infertility evaluation or to rule out a pituitary gland condition.\nProlactin (PRL)\nA prolactin (PRL) test is used to determine the amount of prolactin in the blood. Prolactin is produced\nby the pituitary gland, a small gland near the base of the brain. Prolactin levels are high in pregnant\nwomen and new mothers.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nFollicle Stimulating Hormone (FSH),\nLuteinising Hormone (LH), Prolactin\n(PRL)\nSerum (1ml)\nElectro Chemiluminescence\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n950\n-",
