      "content": "Thyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH)\nTest\nThe Thyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH) test measures the amount of TSH present in the blood. This test helps diagnose the following conditions:\n- Hyperthyroidism :\nOverproduction of thyroid hormones leads to diseases like, excess iodine, Thyroiditis, Benign lumps on\nthe thyroid and Grave’s disease.\n- Hypothyroidism :\nThe underproduction of thyroid The underproduction of thyroid hormones leads to diseases like goiter, postpartum thyroiditis,\nHashimoto’s thyroiditis, etc.\nNo prior preparations are required for the test. A blood sample is drawn from the veins and tested for\nTSH.\nEnquire Now\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nSerum (1ml)\nElectro Chemiluminescence\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n300\nDiagnosis & monitoring hypo\n& hyper thyroidism",
