      "content": "Fertility Profile – II\nTest\nFertility Profile - II\nCouples with secondary infertility have been able to conceive at least once but are now unable to do so.\nFertility Profile - II Tests\nEstradiol (E2)\nA simple blood test to determine the amount of estradiol in a person's blood is an estradiol test.\nFollicle Stimulating Hormone (FSH)\nThis test determines how much follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) is present in your blood.\nLuteinising Hormone (LH)\nThe luteinising hormone (LH) level in your blood is measured by this test.\nProlactin (PRL)\nA prolactin (PRL) test is used to determine the amount of prolactin in the blood. Prolactin is produced\nby the pituitary gland, a small gland near the base of the brain. Prolactin helps the breasts to grow and\nproduce milk throughout pregnancy and after birth.\nThyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH)\nThe hormone Thyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH) stimulates the thyroid gland. A TSH test, which is a\nblood test, is used to assess this hormone.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nEstradiol (E2), Follicle Stimulating\nHormone (FSH), Luteinising Hormone\n(LH), Prolactin (PRL), Thyroid\nStimulating Hormone (TSH)\nSerum (1ml)\nElectro Chemiluminescence\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n1750\n-",
