      "content": "Lipid Profile Cholesterol\nTest\nThis test can determine how much cholesterol and triglycerides are present in your blood.\nLipid Profile Cholesterol Tests\nCholesterol - HDL\nThe level of good cholesterol in your blood is measured by a high-density lipoprotein (HDL) test.\nCholesterol - LDL\nThis test measures Low-density lipoproteins (LDL) is an acronym for low-density lipoproteins.\nTriglycerides\nThe level of triglycerides in your blood is measured by a triglycerides test.\nTotal cholesterol/ HDL ratio\nDivide your total cholesterol value by your HDL cholesterol number to get your cholesterol ratio.\nCholesterol VLDL\nThis test determines how much severely low-density lipoprotein (VLDL) is present in your blood.\nLDL / HDL Ratio\nThe risk increases as the ratio rises. A majority of healthcare providers prefer a ratio of less than 5:1.\nA ratio of less than 3.5:1 is considered excellent.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nLipid Profile Cholesterol –\nTotal, Cholesterol - HDL, Cholesterol\n- LDL, Triglycerides, Total\ncholesterol/ HDL ratio, Cholesterol\nVLDL, LDL / HDL Ratio\nSerum (1ml)\nSpectrophotometry\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n350\n-",
