      "content": "Liver Function Test (LFT)\nTest\nIt is a collection of blood tests that offer information about the status of a patient's liver.\nLiver Function Tests\nAlanine Transaminase (ALT/SGPT)\nThe alanine aminotransferase (ALT) test is a blood test used to see if the liver has been damaged.\nAlbumin, Alkaline Phosphatase (ALP)\nAn alkaline phosphatase (ALP) test determines the level of alkaline phosphatase (ALP) in your blood.\nAspartat Aminotransferase (SGOT)\nThis test may be ordered by your doctor to determine if you have liver disease and to monitor your\ntreatment.\nBilirubin Direct\nIt's used to figure out what's causing symptoms, including jaundice, anaemia, and liver illness.\nBilirubin Total\nIt is frequently included in a panel of tests that assess liver function.\nGlobulin\nGamma globulins and other proteins in your blood are measured in this blood test. It can be used to diagnose a variety of conditions, including immune system disorders and multiple myeloma, a type of cancer.\nProtein Total\nThe total protein test determines the amount of albumin and globulin present in a person’s body.\nBilirubin Indirect\nThis test determines the quantity of bilirubin present in the blood.\nAlbumin/Globulin\nThe albumin/globulin ratio (A/G ratio) is a test that analyses albumin and globulin concentrations in the blood.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nAlanine Transaminase (ALT/SGPT),\nAlbumin, Alkaline Phosphatase (ALP),\nAspartate Aminotransferase (SGOT),\nBilirubin Direct, Bilirubin Total, Globulin,\nProtein Total, Bilirubin Indirect, Albumin\n/ Globulin Ratio\nSerum (1ml)\nSpectrophotometry\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n450\n-",
