      "content": "Thyroid Profile I\nTest\nThyroid blood tests detect if your thyroid gland is functioning well by measuring the quantity of thyroid hormones in your blood.\nThyroid Profile I Tests\nThyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH)\nThe hormone Thyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH) stimulates the thyroid gland. TSH is a blood test that measures this hormone.\nThyroxine - Total (TT4)\nThyroid problems can be diagnosed using a thyroxine test. The thyroid gland is a small butterfly-shaped gland found near the throat.\nTriiodothyronine Total (TT3)\nIt determines the amount of T3 (triiodothyronine) in the blood, part of which is produced directly by the\nthyroid gland.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nThyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH),\nThyroxine - Total (TT4),\nSerum (2 mL)\nElectro Chemiluminescence\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n600\n-",
