      "content": "Master Health Checkup – Female\nTest\nMaster Health Checkup - Female\nMaster Health Checkup - Female tests include the following:\nMaster Health Checkup - Female Tests\nCreatinine\nDoctors check the level of creatinine in the blood through this test, to check kidney function.\nUrea\nThis test is used to determine how well your kidneys are functioning.\nGlucose – FBS & PPBS\nFBS test is to measure Glucose Blood Sugar Levels After Fasting (FBS) and PPBS refers to the test that measures Blood Sugar Levels After a Meal (PPBS).\nComplete Urine Analysis (CUE)\nVarious aberrant elements in urine can be detected with a thorough urine examination.\nLFT\nThese are blood tests that help diagnose and monitor any form of liver illness or damage.\nLipid Profile\nIt is used by doctors to determine the quantity of good and bad cholesterol in the body.\nComplete Blood Count with PS Study (CBC)\nThis test looks at the RBC , WBC, platelets as well as any additional abnormalities like parasites.\nTSH\nThe TSH test measures the amount of thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) in your blood is measured by a TSH test.\nPAP smear\nA Pap smear, often known as a Pap test, is a screening procedure for cervical cancer in women.\nUSG & Chest - XRay\nA chest ultrasound is a noninvasive diagnostic procedure that generates images of the organs and structures of the chest, such as the lungs and mediastinum.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nCreatinine, Urea, Glucose –\nFBS & PPBS, Complete\nUrine Analysis (CUE), LFT,\nLipid Profile, Complete Blood\nCount with PS study\n(CBC),TSH, PAP smear,\nUSG & Chest -XRay\nWB-EDTA (3mL),\nUrine (5mL),Serum (2 mL)\n*RIT\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n3000\n-",
