      "content": "Executive Health Checkup – Male\nTest\nExecutive Health Checkup - Male\nExecutive Health Checkup - Male include the following:\nExecutive Health Checkup - Male Tests\nCreatinine\nNormal results of creatinine tests range from 0.7 to 1.3 mg/dL (61.9 to 114.9 mol/L) for men.\nUrea\nA high level of urea nitrogen in the blood can indicate renal or liver disease.\nGlucose – FBS & PPBS\nIt is a test that determines the amount of sugar in your blood.\nComplete Urine Analysis (CUE)\nA comprehensive urine examination can diagnose kidney disease, urinary tract infections.\nLFT\nThis test provides information about the health of a patient's liver.\nLipid Profile\nA comprehensive cholesterol test is also known as a lipid panel or lipid profile.\nComplete Blood Count (CBC)\nA complete blood count (CBC) is a type of blood test used to evaluate your general health.\nTSH\nThis test determines how well the thyroid gland is functioning.\nPSA\nPSA is a blood test that can be used to identify prostate cancer.\nVitamin D\nThis test can identify whether your vitamin D levels are too high or excessively low.\nPulmonary Functions Test (PFT)\nIt is a thorough evaluation of the respiratory system\nUSG & Chest - XRay\nIt is a great method to determine tuberculosis or pneumonia.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nExecutive Health Checkup -Male Creatinine, Urea, Glucose – FBS & PPBS, Complete\nUrine Analysis (CUE), LFT,\nLipid Profile, Complete Blood\nCount (CBC),TSH, PSA,\nVitamin D, Pulmonary\nFunctions test (PFT), USG &\nChest -XRay\nWB-EDTA (3mL),\nUrine (5mL),Serum (2 mL)\n*RIT\nA/R\nDaily\n4 Hours\n5500\n-",
