      "excerpt": "Urine – Ketone Bodies Test Urine - Ketone Bodies The test measures the amount of ketone present in your urine. Urine - Ketone Bodies Tests Urine-Bile salt & bile pigment The presence of bile pigments in urine can be detected using this test. This test is used...",
      "content": "Urine – Ketone Bodies\nTest\nUrine - Ketone Bodies\nThe test measures the amount of ketone present in your urine.\nUrine - Ketone Bodies Tests\nUrine-Bile salt & bile pigment\nThe presence of bile pigments in urine can be detected using this test. This test is used to diagnose\njaundice, pregnant pruritus, and a variety of liver and kidney problems.\nUrine-Ketone\nThe amount of ketones in the urine is measured by a ketone urine test.\nUrine-Protein\nA normal urine culture measures the number of germs (microorganisms such as bacteria) in the urine.\nUrine-pH\nA urine pH test determines how acidic your urine is.\nUrine-Reducing Substance\nIn most cases, reducing chemicals are not found in urine or faeces. The presence of reducing sugars, such as glucose, lactose, maltose, fructose, and galactose, will be detected by this test.\nTest Table\nTest Parameter\nSample\nMethodology\nTemp.\nSchedule\nReporting\nPrice (INR)\nClinical Information\nUrine (5 ml)\nReagent strip reflectance\nA\nDaily\n4 Hours\n130\n-\nUrine –Bile salt & Bile Pigment\nUrine- Ketone\nUrine -Protein",
